docs.abstract: The former bureau director acknowledged “significant mistakes” in warrants to wiretap a former Trump campaign adviser, days after an inspector general’s report was released.
docs.snippet: The former bureau director acknowledged “significant mistakes” in warrants to wiretap a former Trump campaign adviser, days after an inspector general’s report was released.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — James B. Comey, the former F.B.I. director, acknowledged on Sunday that he was wrong when he said there were no problems with the warrants used to approve surveillance for an adviser to President Trump’s 2016 campaign.

headline.main: Comey Admits Errors in Surveillance Warrants, but Defends F.B.I.

docs.abstract: The diplomats were expelled after they drove onto a base that houses the headquarters of the Navy’s SEAL Team 6. China’s denial of the accusations is the first official acknowledgment of the episode.
docs.snippet: The diplomats were expelled after they drove onto a base that houses the headquarters of the Navy’s SEAL Team 6. China’s denial of the accusations is the first official acknowledgment of the episode.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Chinese government denounced on Monday the United States’ secret expulsion this fall of two Chinese diplomats suspected of espionage, and asked for a reversal of the action. The expulsions appeared to be the first of Chinese diplomats suspected of spying in more than three decades.

headline.main: China Protests U.S. Expulsion of 2 Diplomats Accused of Spying
headline.print_headline: China Protests U.S. Expulsion of Envoys Accused of Spying

docs.abstract: Five days before the government is set to run out of money, lawmakers released the dozen bills needed to keep the government functioning, as well as other provisions.
docs.snippet: Five days before the government is set to run out of money, lawmakers released the dozen bills needed to keep the government functioning, as well as other provisions.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Lawmakers on Monday unveiled a dozen bills that would allocate $1.4 trillion in federal spending for the remainder of the fiscal year to prevent the government from shutting down at midnight on Friday.

headline.main: Spending Deal to Avert Shutdown Carries Key Priorities for Both Parties
headline.print_headline: Bills Would Plug Spending Gap Until Next Fiscal Year

docs.abstract: The legislation underscores an unyielding stream of bipartisan rage at Turkey.
docs.snippet: The legislation underscores an unyielding stream of bipartisan rage at Turkey.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate voted unanimously on Thursday to recognize the Armenian genocide as a matter of American foreign policy, a move that was made over the objections of the Trump administration and that underscored lawmakers’ bipartisan rage at Turkey.

headline.main: Senate Passes Resolution Recognizing Armenian Genocide, in Defiance of Trump
headline.print_headline: Senate Defies White House In Resolution On Genocide

docs.abstract: The high-profile measure would curb the price of prescription drugs and extend more benefits to Medicare beneficiaries.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House, delivering on one of Democrats’ central campaign promises, passed ambitious legislation on Thursday to lower the rising cost of prescription drugs by empowering the federal government to negotiate prices with pharmaceutical manufacturers.

docs.abstract: Trump’s trade adviser invokes his anti-China alter ego to influence the trade debate.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A critical decision about China tariffs is looming, and Ron Vara, Peter Navarro’s hawkish alter ego, has re-emerged to share some thoughts on the matter.

docs.abstract: In June, President Trump promised that millions of undocumented immigrants already in the country would be deported. That didn’t happen.
docs.snippet: In June, President Trump promised that millions of undocumented immigrants already in the country would be deported. That didn’t happen.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Arrests and deportations of undocumented immigrants inside the United States dropped in the past year, according to government data released on Wednesday, a sharp contrast to the “millions” of deportations that President Trump promised this summer.

headline.main: Promises Aside, Deportations Under Trump Dropped in Last Year
headline.print_headline: ICE Arrests Away From Border Declined 10%

docs.abstract: A report by the House Oversight Committee said the Coast Guard had failed to turn around a culture that coddles bullying and was hostile to women and minorities.
docs.snippet: A report by the House Oversight Committee said the Coast Guard had failed to turn around a culture that coddles bullying and was hostile to women and minorities.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Coast Guard has fostered a poor environment for women and minority cadets and has failed to fairly investigate harassment by senior officers and to prevent retaliation against people who report bullying, a House committee said Wednesday.

headline.main: House Inquiry Rebukes Coast Guard for Bullying and Harassment
headline.print_headline: Inquiry Rebukes Coast Guard for Hostile Work Environment
